# IBM Quantum credentials: copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is git-ignored.
#
# Get these from https://quantum.cloud.ibm.com/ after creating an account:
#
#   IBM_QUANTUM_TOKEN     your API key. Required.
#
#   IBM_QUANTUM_INSTANCE  which service instance to bill the job to. OPTIONAL: leave it
#                         blank and the account's accessible instances are selected from
#                         automatically, which is what you want with a single (e.g. free
#                         plan) instance. To pin one, use either its service name or its
#                         CRN, both shown under "Instances" in the dashboard; the CRN
#                         looks like
#                         crn:v1:bluemix:public:quantum-computing:us-east:a/<acct>:<guid>::
#
# Note: the older `ibm_quantum` channel and the `IBMQ` provider no longer exist; this
# project uses the current `ibm_quantum_platform` channel via qiskit-ibm-runtime.
#
# These are only needed for notebooks/03_hardware.ipynb. Everything else (the full
# test suite and all other notebooks) runs on the local simulator with no credentials.

IBM_QUANTUM_TOKEN=
IBM_QUANTUM_INSTANCE=
